---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'Publikationen | Jacek Janczura';
const description =
  'Begutachtete Forschungsarbeiten, Fachartikel und technische Notizen zu KI-Architektur, verteilten Systemen und Software-Engineering.';
const lang = 'de';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} lang={lang}>
  <section class="notes-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Publikationen</h1>
      <p class="notes-subtitle">
        Begutachtete Forschung, Fachartikel und technische Einblicke
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="notes-content">
    <div class="container content">
      <!-- Publications Section -->
      <div class="publications-section">
        <h2>Publikationen & Beiträge</h2>
        <div class="publications-grid">
          <div class="publication-group">
            <h3>Begutachtete Veröffentlichungen</h3>
            <article class="publication-card">
              <h4>
                Saluki: Finding Taint-style Vulnerabilities with Static Property
                Checking
              </h4>
              <p>
                BAR/NDSS Workshop 2018. Ein Forschungstool zur Erkennung von
                Taint-basierten Sicherheitslücken in Binärcode — kombiniert
                statische Analyse mit dynamischem Taint-Tracking. Bietet eine
                DSL für Taint-Policies und wurde an realen Programmen erprobt.
              </p>
              <p>
                <strong>Rolle:</strong> Autor und Maintainer des Repositories.
                <strong>Links:</strong>
                <a
                  href="https://github.com/jjanczur/Saluki"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub-Repository</a
                >
                <a
                  href="https://www.ndss-symposium.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/bar2018_19_Gotovchits_paper.pdf"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer">Paper</a
                >
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="publication-card">
              <h4>
                DeCoCo: Blockchain-based Decentralized Compensation of Digital
                Content Purchases
              </h4>
              <p>
                IEEE BRAINS 2020. Ein Blockchain-basierter, dezentraler
                Vergütungsmechanismus für digitale Inhalte mit transparenten,
                programmierbaren Auszahlungen und Smart-Contract-Architektur.
              </p>
              <p>
                <strong>Rolle:</strong> Autor/Co-Autor. <strong>DOI:</strong>
                <a
                  href="https://doi.org/10.1109/BRAINS49436.2020.9223299"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer">10.1109/BRAINS49436.2020.9223299</a
                >
                <a
                  href="https://www.researchgate.net/publication/347575008_DeCoCo_Blockchain-based_Decentralized_Compensation_of_Digital_Content_Purchases"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer">ResearchGate</a
                >
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
          <div class="publication-group">
            <h3>Artikel & Anleitungen</h3>
            <article class="publication-card">
              <h4>Utility NFTs more than simple JPEGs?</h4>
              <p>
                Medium, 1. Februar 2023. Definiert „Utility-NFTs" und zeigt
                deren praktischen Nutzen jenseits reiner Sammlerstücke — etwa
                als Zugangsberechtigungen oder Rollen. Mit Implikationen für
                NFT-Marktplätze.
              </p>
              <p>
                <strong>Link:</strong>
                <a
                  href="https://medium.com/@jacekjanczura/utility-nfts-more-than-simple-jpegs-janczura-382a78e540d4"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer">Medium-Artikel</a
                >
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="publication-card">
              <h4>How to run your python code in KnowledgeX</h4>
              <p>
                Medium, 17. Februar 2022. Anleitung zur Ausführung von
                Python-Jobs auf KnowledgeX via iExec und TEE. Behandelt
                Docker-Templates, Worker-Verifikation und Auditierbarkeit für
                Entwickler und Data Scientists.
              </p>
              <p>
                <strong>Link:</strong>
                <a
                  href="https://blog.knowledgex.eu/how-to-run-your-python-code-in-knowledgex-749e2651370c"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer">Blogbeitrag</a
                >
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="publication-card">
              <h4>REL_2020_02_APP_web.pdf</h4>
              <p>
                <strong>Vorläufig:</strong> Titel und Abstract noch ausstehend.
                [Bestätigung aus Originalquelle erforderlich].
              </p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Notes Section -->
      <div class="notes-section">
        <h2>Technische Notizen</h2>
        <div class="notes-intro">
          <p>
            Gelegentliche technische Notizen und Erkenntnisse aus der Arbeit mit
            KI-Systemen, verteilten Architekturen und Enterprise-Software.
            Weniger formal als Vorträge, aber mit wertvollen Beobachtungen aus
            der Praxis.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="notes-grid">
          <article class="note-card">
            <div class="note-header">
              <h2>Prompt Engineering im Unternehmenseinsatz</h2>
              <span class="note-date">2024-02-15</span>
            </div>
            <p class="note-excerpt">
              Wie man ein Prompt-Optimierungssystem aufbaut, das teamübergreifend
              skaliert und konsistente KI-Ergebnisse liefert. Erkenntnisse aus
              der Entwicklung eines „Prompt-Assistenten" für
              Enterprise-Anwendungsfälle.
            </p>
            <div class="note-tags">
              <span class="tag">Prompt Engineering</span>
              <span class="tag">KI-Governance</span>
              <span class="tag">Enterprise</span>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="note-card">
            <div class="note-header">
              <h2>Event-Driven KI-Pipelines</h2>
              <span class="note-date">2024-01-22</span>
            </div>
            <p class="note-excerpt">
              Design robuster KI-Workflows mit ereignisgesteuerten
              Architekturmustern. Wie SQS/SNS den Backpressure in KI-Pipelines
              abfedern und zuverlässige Verarbeitung sicherstellen.
            </p>
            <div class="note-tags">
              <span class="tag">Event-Driven</span>
              <span class="tag">KI-Pipelines</span>
              <span class="tag">AWS</span>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="note-card">
            <div class="note-header">
              <h2>Multi-Modell-Routing für KI</h2>
              <span class="note-date">2023-12-10</span>
            </div>
            <p class="note-excerpt">
              Intelligente Routing-Strategien für Multi-Modell-KI-Deployments.
              Kostenoptimierung bei gleichzeitig hoher Performance und Qualität
              — über verschiedene Modellanbieter hinweg.
            </p>
            <div class="note-tags">
              <span class="tag">Multi-Modell</span>
              <span class="tag">Kostenoptimierung</span>
              <span class="tag">Architektur</span>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="note-card">
            <div class="note-header">
              <h2>Sicherheit für KI-Plattformen</h2>
              <span class="note-date">2023-11-18</span>
            </div>
            <p class="note-excerpt">
              Zentrale Sicherheitsaspekte für KI-Plattformen: Datenschutz,
              Zugriffskontrolle, Audit-Trails und automatisierte Compliance in
              KI-first-Anwendungen.
            </p>
            <div class="note-tags">
              <span class="tag">KI-Sicherheit</span>
              <span class="tag">Compliance</span>
              <span class="tag">Datenschutz</span>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>


<style>
  .notes-hero {
    padding: var(--space-8) 0;
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--bg) 0%,
      oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.05) 30%,
      oklch(from var(--accent) l c h / 0.03) 60%,
      var(--muted) 100%
    );
    text-align: center;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .notes-hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(
      ellipse at top right,
      oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.08) 0%,
      transparent 50%
    );
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }

  .notes-hero .container {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .notes-hero h1 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-hero);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--text) 0%,
      var(--primary) 50%,
      var(--text) 100%
    );
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-size: 200% auto;
    animation: gradient-shift 8s ease infinite;
  }

  @keyframes gradient-shift {
    0%,
    100% {
      background-position: 0% center;
    }
    50% {
      background-position: 100% center;
    }
  }

  .notes-subtitle {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary) 0%, var(--accent) 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    max-width: var(--content-width);
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }

  .notes-content {
    padding: var(--space-8) 0;
    background: linear-gradient(
      180deg,
      var(--bg) 0%,
      oklch(from var(--muted) l c h / 0.3) 50%,
      var(--bg) 100%
    );
  }

  .notes-intro {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .notes-intro p {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    max-width: var(--content-width);
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .notes-section {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
  }

  .notes-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    text-align: center;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary) 0%, var(--accent) 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
  }

  .notes-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-5);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .note-card {
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--bg) 0%,
      oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.02) 100%
    );
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    border-radius: var(--radius-l);
    padding: var(--space-5);
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .note-card::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 4px;
    background: linear-gradient(
      90deg,
      var(--primary),
      var(--accent),
      var(--primary)
    );
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
  }

  .note-card::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.05) 0%,
      transparent 100%
    );
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .note-card:hover {
    border-color: oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.3);
    box-shadow:
      0 8px 24px oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.15),
      var(--shadow-2);
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--bg) 0%,
      oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.05) 100%
    );
  }

  .note-card:hover::before {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .note-card:hover::after {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .note-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .note-header h2 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xl);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary) 0%, var(--accent) 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2) 0;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .note-date {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--text);
    opacity: 0.8;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-normal);
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2);
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--muted) 0%,
      oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.03) 100%
    );
    border-radius: var(--radius-s);
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .note-excerpt {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4) 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text);
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .note-tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .tag {
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--muted) 0%,
      oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.1) 100%
    );
    color: var(--primary);
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
    border-radius: var(--radius-s);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }

  .tag:hover {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary) 0%, var(--accent) 100%);
    color: white;
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.3);
  }

  .publications-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .publications-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    text-align: center;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary) 0%, var(--accent) 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
  }

  .publications-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(400px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .publication-group h3 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary) 0%, var(--accent) 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
  }

  .publication-card {
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--bg) 0%,
      oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.02) 100%
    );
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    border-radius: var(--radius-l);
    padding: var(--space-5);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .publication-card::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 3px;
    background: linear-gradient(
      90deg,
      var(--primary),
      var(--accent),
      var(--primary)
    );
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
  }

  .publication-card:hover {
    border-color: oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.3);
    box-shadow:
      0 6px 20px oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.12),
      var(--shadow-1);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--bg) 0%,
      oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.04) 100%
    );
  }

  .publication-card:hover::before {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .publication-card h4 {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary) 0%, var(--accent) 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .publication-card p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .publication-card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .publication-card a {
    color: var(--primary);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-s);
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
    display: inline-block;
    margin-right: var(--space-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.1) 0%,
      oklch(from var(--accent) l c h / 0.05) 100%
    );
    border: 1px solid transparent;
  }

  .publication-card a:hover {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary) 0%, var(--accent) 100%);
    color: white;
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px oklch(from var(--primary) l c h / 0.3);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .publication-card strong {
    color: var(--primary);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .notes-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .publications-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
